item.title: Debug strings?
item.dc:creator: @Jython super_
item.description:
@Jython wrote:

[quote=“Kosaki, post:10, topic:294974”]This has been here for quite some time, I first noticed it in #530 or so.

Me and Syntax played with it at that time and you can’t really do very much. You can do different things like check location, debug memory, disable tweening, check cache (how many player models are loaded and such), garbage collect and such. You can also make it paint debug info on screen.

All you need to do to activate it is to change the int at the top of the code to a lower number and you will have access to the commands. But when you do so the action system will be disabled, but you can also avoid that tho.[/quote]

I don’t think you understand us big boys… everyone and their mother knows about the commands. They have KNOWN about the commands. The post is showing that the morons left in debug info, which could potentially help us refactor. Silly JAGeX.

item.title: Debug strings?
item.dc:creator: @Kosaki Kosaki
item.description:
@Kosaki wrote:

This has been here for quite some time, I first noticed it in #530 or so.

Me and Syntax played with it at that time and you can’t really do very much. You can do different things like check location, debug memory, disable tweening, check cache (how many player models are loaded and such), garbage collect and such. You can also make it paint debug info on screen.

All you need to do to activate it is to change the int at the top of the code to a lower number and you will have access to the commands. But when you do so the action system will be disabled, but you can also avoid that tho.
